               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary>                     <p>This small, palm leaf manuscript contains the complete text of the <title xml:lang="sa">Brahmasūtra</title>, in Nandināgarī script. Each <term xml:lang="sa">sūtra</term> is preceded and followed by <quote xml:lang="sa">oṃ</quote>. Although the title folio reads <title xml:lang="sa">Sūtrabhāṣya</title>, the <term xml:lang="sa">sūtra</term>s are presented without commentary.</p>
<p>The <title xml:lang="sa">Brahmasūtra</title> is usually attributed to <persName xml:lang="sa">Bādarāyaṇa</persName>, who is sometimes called <persName xml:lang="sa">Vyāsa</persName>. In the final rubric of this manuscript, the text is attributed to <persName xml:lang="sa">Kṛṣṇadvaipāyana</persName>, the traditional author of the <title xml:lang="sa">Mahābhārata</title>, who is also known as <persName xml:lang="sa">Vyāsa</persName>.</p>
                  </summary>
                  
               <msItem synch="#mūla" defective="false"><title xml:lang="sa">Brahmasūtra</title><author xml:lang="sa">Bādarāyaṇa</author><textLang mainLang="san"/><rubric xml:lang="sa"><milestone n="1r" facs="4" unit="folio"/>śrīvedavyāsāya namaḥ hariḥ oṃ |</rubric><incipit xml:lang="sa"><milestone n="1r" facs="4" unit="folio"/>oṃ athāto braṃhmajijñāsā oṃ | <lb n="2"/>oṃ janmādyasya yataḥ oṃ |</incipit><explicit xml:lang="sa"><milestone n="25v" facs="53" unit="folio"/> <lb n="6"/><gap reason="ellipsis"/>oṃ anāvṛttiś śabdād anāvṛttiś śa<lb n="7"/>bdāt_ oṃ || - ||</explicit><finalRubric xml:lang="sa"><milestone n="25v" facs="53" unit="folio"/> <lb n="7"/>iti śrīmatkṛṣṇadvaipāyanakṛtabraṃhmasūtreṣu caturthādhyā<pb n="26r" facs="54"/>yasya caturthaḥ pāraḥ || - ||</finalRubric><colophon xml:lang="sa"><milestone n="26r" facs="54" unit="folio"/>śrīkṛṣṇārpaṇam astu || - || hariḥ oṃ || samā<lb n="2"/>ptaś cāyaṃ graṃthaḥ || | - || ❈ || - || śrīvedavyāsāya namaḥ || śrīhayagrīvāya namaḥ || - ||</colophon></msItem></msContents>
